<dd>2. face; encounter</dd><br>
<dd>좋지 않은 상황을 직접 당하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To come to face a bad situation oneself.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>맞서다 [맏써다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. face; confront; stand face to face</dd><br>
<dd>서로 마주 보고 서다.</dd><br>
<dd>To stand facing each other.</dd><br>
<dd>2. stand against; rise against</dd><br>
<dd>서로 겨루어 굽히지 않고 버티다.</dd><br>
<dd>To compete against each other and not give in.</dd><br>
<dd>3. accept; not give in</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 상황을 받아들이거나 그 상황에 굽히지 않고 버티다.</dd><br>
<dd>To accept a certain situation or bear the situation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>맞보다 [맏뽀다]</dt><br>
<dd>face; see each other in the face</dd><br>
<dd>마주 대하여 보다.</dd><br>
<dd>To face each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>맞바라보다 [맏빠라보다]</dt><br>
<dd>face; see each other in the face</dd><br>
<dd>마주 향하여 보다.</dd><br>
<dd>To face each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>맞대다 [맏때다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. face</dd><br>
<dd>서로 가깝게 마주 대하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To face each other closely.</dd><br>
<dd>2. compare</dd><br>
<dd>같은 자격으로 서로 비교하다.</dd><br>
<dd>For two people of the same qualification to compare each other.</dd><br>
<dd>3. touch</dd><br>
<dd>서로 마주 닿게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To make two people or things touch each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>맞다 [맏따]</dt><br>
<dd>1. receive</dd><br>
<dd>오는 사람을 예의를 갖추어 받아들이다.</dd><br>
<dd>To politely receive someone who comes.</dd><br>
<dd>2. deal with; treat</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 사람이나 세력을 상대하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To deal with a certain individual or group.</dd><br>
<dd>3. face; meet; greet</dd><br>
<dd>시간이 지나서 오는 때를 대하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To face a specific moment as time passes by.</dd><br>
<dd>4. be exposed to</dd><br>
<dd>내리는 눈이나 비 등이 닿는 것을 그대로 받다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be touched by snow, rain, etc., as it falls.</dd><br>
<dd>5. receive; get</dd><br>
<dd>점수를 받다.</dd><br>
<dd>To receive a grade.</dd><br>
<dd>6. become a victim</dd><br>
<dd>좋지 않은 일을 당하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To become the victim of a bad incident.</dd><br>
<dd>7. take; accept</dd><br>
<dd>식구로 받아들이다.</dd><br>
<dd>To accept someone as a family member.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>만나다 [만나다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. meet; join</dd><br>
<dd>선이나 길, 강 등이 서로 마주 닿거나 연결되다.</dd><br>
<dd>For a line, road, river, etc. to adjoin or be connected with each other.</dd><br>
<dd>2. meet; meet with; join</dd><br>
<dd>누군가 가거나 와서 둘이 서로 마주 대하다.</dd><br>
<dd>For one of two to go or come and be face to face with the other.</dd><br>
<dd>3. meet with; encounter; come across; be exposed to; face; confront</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 사실이나 사물을 눈앞에 대하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To face a fact or object in front of one's eyes.</dd><br>
<dd>4. meet with; be struck by; be hit by; go through; suffer</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 당하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To go through something.</dd><br>
<dd>5. be struck by; be hit by</dd><br>
<dd>어디를 가는 도중에 비, 눈, 바람 등을 맞다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be struck by rain, snow, wind on one's way to somewhere.</dd><br>
<dd>6. be in; enjoy; suffer; meet</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 때를 당하거나 어떤 기회를 얻다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be in a certain time or gain an opportunity.</dd><br>
<dd>7. run into; bump into; come across; run across</dd><br>
<dd>어디를 가는 도중에 누구와 우연히 마주치다.</dd><br>
<dd>To meet someone accidently on one's way somewhere.</dd><br>
<dd>8. run into; bump into; come across; run across; come to see; come in sight of</dd><br>
<dd>어디를 가는 도중에 무엇을 우연히 발견하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To discover something accidently on one's way somewhere.</dd><br>
<dd>9. be tied with; be intertwined with</dd><br>
<dd>인연이 있어 어떤 관계를 맺다.</dd><br>
<dd>To have a certain relationship with someone based on a connection.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>마주치다 [마주치다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. crash against; collide; run against</dd><br>
<dd>서로 똑바로 부딪치다.</dd><br>
<dd>For two objects to crash into each other head-on.</dd><br>
<dd>2. happen to meet; run across</dd><br>
<dd>우연히 서로 만나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For two people to meet by chance.</dd><br>
<dd>3. (eyes) meet</dd><br>
<dd>눈길이 서로 닿다.</dd><br>
<dd>For glances to meet.</dd><br>
<dd>4. face</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 경우나 처지에 당하게 되다.</dd><br>
<dd>To face an occasion or situation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>대하다 [대ː하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. face; confront</dd><br>
<dd>마주 향해 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be face to face.</dd><br>
<dd>2. handle; deal with</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 태도로 상대하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To handle with a certain attitude.</dd><br>
<dd>3. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>대상이나 상대로 삼다.</dd><br>
<dd>To consider as a counterpart or opponent.</dd><br>
<dd>4. enjoy; appreciate</dd><br>
<dd>작품 등을 직접 읽거나 감상하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To read or appreciate a piece of art, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>대면하다 [대ː면하다]</dt><br>
<dd>meet; face</dd><br>
<dd>직접 얼굴을 보며 만나다.</dd><br>
<dd>To meet face to face.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>당면하다 [당면하다]</dt><br>
<dd>confront; face</dd><br>
<dd>처리해야 할 일을 바로 앞에 만나게 되다.</dd><br>
<dd>To face a matter that has to be dealt with.</dd><br>
